{"url": "http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2016/06/24/stocks-fall-brexit_n_10655236.html", "date": "2016-06-24", "content": "June 24 (Reuters) - U.S. stock indexes opened sharply lower on Friday after Britain voted to leave the European Union, sparking turmoil in markets unseen since the 2008 financial crisis.\nInvestors fled to safe-harbor assets such as gold and U.S. Treasury bonds, while dumping risky ones such as equities and oil.\nThe Dow Jones industrial average was down 243.04 points, or 1.35 percent, at 17,768.03, the S&P 500 34.25 points, or 1.62 percent, at 2,079.07 and the Nasdaq composite 192.73 points, or 3.93 percent, at 4,717.31. (Reporting by Yashaswini Swamynathan in Bengaluru; Editing by Saumyadeb Chakrabarty)", "title": "U.S. Stocks Fall After 'Brexit' Vote"}